\pard\f0\fs28 Two fairly well-marked variants sometimes cause difficulty in identifying this species: var.{\i  microsperma} (Willk.) Heywood has more shortly cucullate sepals and seeds less than 2 mm, and var.{\i  cavanillesiana} (Font Quer & A. Bolos) Heywood has seeds broadly crispate-winged.
\par

