\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. M. foetida} Bourgeau ex Cosson, {\i Not. Pl. Crit.} 143 (1852). Stems much branched from the base. Lower leaves obovate; upper cauline leaves minute, triangular-ovate, very acute to acuminate. Raceme 5- to 12-flowered; sepals all obtuse; petals 12 mm, whitish. Siliqua 40-60 × 1·5-2 mm, compressed, 4-angled, long-pedicellate. Seeds c. 1·5 mm, brownish, uniseriate, distinctly white-margined.{\i  Base-rich soils. • S. & S.E. Spain.} Hs.
